Orlando Pirates midfielder Ben Motshwari has fully recovered from the Covid-19 virus, the Soweto giants confirmed on Monday. The 29-year-old became the first Premier Soccer League (PSL) player to contract the coronavirus, having reportedly been infected while shopping. In a 30-second video on the club's official Twitter account, Motshwari urged the South African public to continue to sanitise their hands and practice safe social distancing. 